org.ecoinformatics.seek.querybuilder

Class DBWhereModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.AbstractListModel
      • org.ecoinformatics.seek.querybuilder.DBWhereModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.ListModel

    public class DBWhereModel
extends javax.swing.AbstractListModel
    This class represents the model for the JList class. The complexity here is that the model want to view everything as a a vector, but the items are actually an object tree. So the options where to:
    1) Use a vecotr as the model and add the complexity to the add and remove methods (this is what was done) 2) Use the "real" data model and then when an item was asked for by index we traverse the tree to figure out the index each time.

    Assuming painting occurs more often than model updates I went with approach number one
